snippet.title: Esri Geodatabase - 2- Unversioned Datasets
snippet.description:
Full Multi-User Geodatabase Playlist https://goo.gl/nSgYnM

This episode, we will learn about the different types of multiuser geodatabases. Non-Versioned/No Archiving, Non-Versioned/with Archiving, Versioned/No Archiving, Versioned/With Archiving. We briefly discuss long transactions and migrate our Phonatech geodatabase from File to Non-Versioned. We then do necessary changes to our code to connect and consume the new geodatabase.

snippet.title: Esri Geodatabase - Read phenomenas, Version Trees, Access controls
snippet.description:
Full Multi-User Geodatabase Playlist https://goo.gl/nSgYnM


Happy holidays! 

In this episode, we talk about different read phenomenas that occurs when you lack proper isolation, like dirty reads and non-repeatable reads.  How to create a version, change a version, make edits. We also explain the version trees and illustrate the access levels. Finally we talk about the IVersion interface and how we use it to get the version name from ArcObjects.

snippet.title: Setting up a PostgreSQL Instance on Linux to work wth ArcGIS
snippet.description:
We discuss how to setup postgres instance from scratch on Ubuntu 16.04.2 LTS, configure the instance to work with ArcGIS and then create an enterprise geodatabase from ArcGIS Desktop and finally we connect to the geodatabase. 


Steps to Install Postgres

Ubuntu 16.0.4
https://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop

Enable older postgres versions on the ubuntu
https://www.postgresql.org/download/linux/ubuntu/

Install Open SSH so putty can connect to ubuntu
install openssh-server

Install postgres 9.4
apt-get install postgresql-9.4

Change postgres password
sudo -u postgres psql
alter user postgres password 'password';

Set permissions 
chmod 777 usr/lib/postgresql/9.4/lib

Allow remote connections

sudo gedit /etc/postgresql/9.4/main/pg_hba.conf
host all all all md5

sudo gedit /etc/postgresql/9.4/main/postgresql.conf 
listenaddress=‘*’


download putty on Windows machine to copy the st_geometry.so file

http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/latest.html

pscp.exe st_geometry.so ig@pg:/usr/lib/postgresql/9.4/lib

where ig is the ubuntu user, pg is the ubuntu machine

Enjoy!

snippet.title: Spinning ArcGIS Enterprise Geodatabase on Docker container
snippet.description:
Full Multi-User Geodatabase Playlist https://goo.gl/nSgYnM

Docker is a great technology that allows you to host your application in small jails of memory called containers. 

We use this technology to quickly spin up a postgres instance that has all the neccessary requirements to create enterprise geodatabase. 

https://hub.docker.com/r/husseinnasser/arcgispg/

-----
To pull ArcGIS 10.5 compatible docker container of postgres (9.5). This command will pull and run a container.

docker run --rm -p 5432:5432 husseinnasser/arcgispg:105



To pull ArcGIS 10.4.1 compatible docker container of postgres (9.4) This command will pull and run a container.

docker run --rm -p 5432:5432 husseinnasser/arcgispg:1041
